<http://www.spektrix.com/tarragontheatre/event/18001AQNDJSHVVQBLCSKTRHMGHNPJGJTM>
  a schema:Event;
  schema:name "Bachelor Man (Guest Presentation)";
  schema:description """
	<h1>Bachelor Man</h1><span><br/></span>Written by Winston Kam<span><br/></span>Directed by Brenda Kamino with Diana Belshaw<span><br/></span><span><br/></span>It’s July 1st, 1929, Dominion Day, known as ‘Humiliation Day’ in John’s Toronto Chinatown teahouse where his regulars take refuge. It’s the 6th anniversary of the Exclusion Act, which prevented the wives and families of Chinese men, who came to Canada largely to build the railroad, from joining them. How did this Bachelor Society survive? This gritty and poetic depiction unveils a microcosm of Chinatown- including a one-armed WWI vet, a half Chinese scholar, a teenage stowaway, - during the twenty-four years that the Canadian Government prohibited Chinese immigration.<span><br/></span><span><br/></span>Featuring:<span><br/></span>Brenda Kamino, Sean Baek, Robert Lee, Oliver Koomsatira, Micah Chu, Renée Wong, Ziye Hu, George Chiang<span><br/></span><span><br/></span>Produced by Renaissance Canadian Theatre Company, to learn more visit <a target=\"_blank\" href=\"https://renaissancetheatre.wordpress.com/about/\">renaissancetheatre.wordpress.com</a>
""";
  schema:startDate "2025-09-02T19:30:00"^^xsd:dateTime;
  schema:image <https://system.spektrix.com/tarragontheatre/files/9afeb2a7-e124-437e-b864-a5cc73845ff8.jpg>;
  schema:location <https://spektrix.com/tarragontheatre/location/801ARDQDDMGGJKKRTNTJBMCCMMBCPQKCR>;
  schema:organizer <https://spektrix.com/tarragontheatre/organization/tarragon-theatre>;
  schema:offers _:27f0623284aa408d9fe9a7f2081ff7885590;
  schema:duration "PT105M";
  schema:endDate "2025-09-02T21:15:00"^^xsd:dateTime .

