<http://www.spektrix.com/tarragontheatre/event/12001ALNGHTPHGCKCMSTDNQBDRDVTJPQB>
  a schema:Event;
  schema:name "cicadas";
  schema:description """
	<h1>cicadas</h1>Created by Chris Thornborrow and David Yee<span><br/></span>Directed by Nina Lee Aquino<span><br/></span><span><br/></span>World Premiere<span><br/></span>A Tarragon Theatre and NAC English Theatre Co-Production<span><br/></span><span><br/></span>In 2032, while on the hunt for a new home in Toronto’s Trinity Bellwoods, Trim and Janie are drawn to a very peculiar house. A flood with no leak, an ominous voice, and hordes of cicadas are only three of the many strange things seeping up through the old floorboards. Could a strangely luminous painting unlock long-hidden secrets of what lies beneath the home?<span><br/></span><span><br/></span>Howling winds, storms, and the ever-present sound of cicadas remind us that nothing stays buried.<span><br/></span><span><br/></span><span class=\"ItalicText\"><span class=\"BoldText\">cicadas</span></span> is a modern eco-thriller from the minds of Governor General's Award and Siminovitch Prize laureate David Yee and award-winning composer Chris Thornborrow that serves as both mystery and warning.
""";
