<http://www.spektrix.com/tarragontheatre/event/26202ACGMMQQPMLRTMJGDSSHKNCHJVBNT>
  a schema:Event;
  schema:name "Cleo (Tarragon X TMU)";
  schema:description """
	<h1>Cleo</h1>written and directed by Makram Ayache<span><br/></span><span><br/></span>You think you know the story of Egypt's favorite queen, Cleopatra? In <span class=\"ItalicText\">Cleo</span>, Cleo is an 18 year old Egyptian transfer student at Actium High, a private school in North America. Enemies are made, alliances are tested, and the battle between Cleo and Octavia for Student Union President becomes an all out war in this dramedy about the struggle for love and power.<span><br/></span><span><br/></span><h2>Tarragon x TMU</h2>Performance at The Creative School and Tarragon Theatre collaborate on two workshop projects which support the development of new work, featuring the graduating class of Performance Acting students.<span><br/></span><span><br/></span><span class=\"BoldText\">Please Note:</span> <span class=\"ItalicText\">Cleo</span> contains strobe lighting and includes some sensitive themes, if you want to know more, <a target=\"_top\" href=\"https://tarragontheatre.com/plays/uncategorized/tarragonxtmu/\">visit our website.</a>
""";
