<http://www.spektrix.com/tarragontheatre/event/27601AQVLTVTCJRHPTLCPRBPBJCDTNLPC>
  a schema:Event;
  schema:name "Pearle Harbour's Agit-Pop! (Greenhouse Festival)";
  schema:description """
	<h1>AGIT-POP!</h1><span><br/></span><h2>A Special Presentation at the Greenhouse Festival</h2><span><br/></span><span class=\"ItalicText\"><span class=\"BoldText\">Greenhouse Festival Passholders save 20%!</span></span><span><br/></span><span><br/></span>Think Judy Garland at Carnegie. On acid.<span><br/></span><span><br/></span>The clock is ticking, time is running out, and the end is nigher than it’s ever been before. In <span class=\"ItalicText\">Agit-Pop!</span> Pearle takes on the world, weaving her acid wit and demented storytelling through the most anxiety-inducing headlines ripped from the daily rag. It's a cabaret fit for Doomsday.<span><br/></span><span><br/></span>Paired with bold re-imaginings of the biggest hits of the 20th century (musical director Stella Conway), Pearle sings the songs of David Bowie, Britney Spears, the Beach Boys, and more, as you’ve never heard them before.<span><br/></span><span><br/></span><span class=\"ItalicText\">Agit-Pop!</span> has toured to every coast of Canada, from thousand-seat vaudeville theatres to concert halls to defunct sex clubs.<span><br/></span><span><br/></span><span><br/></span><span class=\"BoldText\">PEARLE HARBOUR</span> is an award-winning drag performance artist, a gonzo-theatre maker, and Canada’s premiere tragicomedienne. Her audience-centric work aims to celebrate the radical and transformative potential of collective experience.<span><br/></span><span><br/></span>\"Pearle has emerged as one of the most engaging, thoughtful performance artists around.”<span><br/></span>– <span class=\"ItalicText\">GLENN SUMI, NOW MAGAZINE</span><span><br/></span><span><br/></span>
""";
  schema:startDate "2026-01-30T21:15:00"^^xsd:dateTime;
  schema:image <https://system.spektrix.com/tarragontheatre/files/a5c9142f-0c7a-43db-9c8b-4a457d668832.jpg>;
  schema:location <https://spektrix.com/tarragontheatre/location/801ARDQDDMGGJKKRTNTJBMCCMMBCPQKCR>;
  schema:organizer <https://spektrix.com/tarragontheatre/organization/tarragon-theatre>;
