<http://www.spektrix.com/tarragontheatre/event/34801AJDHTGHVDDDGHKMHBRJLKTRHLMSR>
  a schema:Event;
  schema:name "You’re Still Here";
  schema:description """
	<h1><span class=\"BoldText\">You’re Still Here</span></h1><span><br/></span>Written by Katherine Gauthier<span><br/></span>Directed by Andrew Kushnir<span><br/></span>World Premiere<span><br/></span>Mainspace<span><br/></span><span><br/></span>March 23 - April 18, 2027<span><br/></span><span><br/></span>A new medical technology tests the impossible: accurately predicting when a person will die. When it is quietly introduced into a hospice, Dr. Froese, a leading palliative care physician, must navigate the ethical and emotional tremors it sends through his daily life. <span><br/></span><span><br/></span>What does it mean to live, knowing when we’ll die? <span><br/></span><span><br/></span><span class=\"ItalicText\">You’re Still Here</span> examines the cost of knowing too much, and the ways medicine shapes our understanding of dying, asking how we measure a life when the end is no longer abstract.<span><br/></span><span><br/></span><span class=\"ItalicText\">\"Kat’s work...marches head-on into complicated, risky and challenging subject matter with delicacy, integrity and deep care.\"</span><span><br/></span>-Toronto Guardian<span><br/></span>
""";
